eir more famous neighbors, the monks of Dijon, this edition recounts the history of one of the oldest houses in Burgundy and gives it its proper due.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aMonasticism and religious orders. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aBenedictine monks.  aBèze.  aMedieval monasticism.  acartulary.  ahistory of Burgundy.  amedieval French history.  amedieval chronicles.  amedieval historiography.  amedieval memory.  amedieval monks.1 aBouchard, Constance Brittain, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP eBook-Package Pilot 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753351940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487533519423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487533519.jpg  a978-3-11-065206-2  UTP eBook-Package Pilot 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEGb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020